Pours copper clear with big, beige head. Aroma is great and intensive smoked notes - smoked cheese, meat, fireplace. Taste is pithy, grainy sweetness and smoke. Reminds sandwich with smoked meat. Body is full, carbonation is low. Average bitterness.

UPDATED: APR 21, 2009 Even better than the MÃ¤rzen, which was already excellent. Lovely deep color, smells a bit like rye-bread. Tastes like bottled smoke with a hint of liquorice. Nice bitter in the finish. Not quite as warming as I expected.
Re-rated from tap @ Mallaskukko;
Dark like tar, minimal brown head. Very smoky aroma, roasted maltiness. Tastes like liquid tar and smoke, tons of liquorice. Semi-oily feel. A little ashy in finish. Warms you up more than the bottled version, still without the burn of alcohol.
